  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  All consented adults (age &gt; 18), with the diagnosis of CHILD A cirrhosis with MELD
             score of &lt; 10.

          -  Diagnosis of liver cirrhosis as documented by liver biopsy (stage IV) and / or
             fibroscan (score &gt; 12 kpa) and / or fibrotest (score &gt; 0.74) and /or imaging.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  History of &gt; grade II hepatic encephalopathy (HE).

          -  Diagnosis of dementia, Parkinson disease, Schizophrenia (Patients with major
             depression will be noted but not excluded).

          -  Use of sedatives, tranquilizers or anti- psychotic medication during and/or 2 weeks
             prior to enrolling Use of antibiotics for any length of period during and/or 2 weeks
             prior to enrolling.

          -  Current use of lactulose or neomycin.

          -  Use of alcohol or elicit drugs during and/ or 6 months prior to enrolling.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
